definition.value: A propenol in which the C=C bond connects C-2 and C-3. It is has been found in garlic (Allium sativum). Formerly used as a herbicide for the control of various grass and weed seeds.
Benzene substituted at the 1,2, and 4 positions by carboxy groups.
The N-benzoyl-4-hydroxy derivative of anthranilic acid.
An  aminoimidazole  that is 1H-imidazole substituted by an amino group at position 4.
A cholestanoid that is 5alpha-cholestane substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 3.
